WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.952 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:02.952 --> 00:00:20.159 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.159 --> 00:00:21.950 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:21.950 --> 00:00:24.530 align:middle line:10%
You know, we talk a lot on this
program about the afterlife.

00:00:24.530 --> 00:00:26.780 align:middle line:10%
And we're going to do that
now with a different twist,

00:00:26.780 --> 00:00:29.540 align:middle line:10%
a different perspective,
with Richard Martini,

00:00:29.540 --> 00:00:31.610 align:middle line:10%
noted author, researcher.

00:00:31.610 --> 00:00:33.860 align:middle line:10%
And he's back on
"Beyond Belief."

00:00:33.860 --> 00:00:35.349 align:middle line:90%
Richard, always good to see you.

00:00:35.349 --> 00:00:37.640 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHARD MARTINI: It's always
good to see you, George.

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:42.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You've always done so
remarkable things, great work.

00:00:42.180 --> 00:00:46.310 align:middle line:84%
You've investigated the
life of Amelia Earhart.

00:00:46.310 --> 00:00:50.780 align:middle line:84%
But tonight, we're going to
talk about the afterlife.

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:52.594 align:middle line:84%
What do people generally
think about that?

00:00:52.594 --> 00:00:53.760 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Well, it's funny.

00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Because you gave me that
moniker, the afterlife expert.

00:00:57.440 --> 00:00:58.320 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, wow.

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.120 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:00:59.120 --> 00:00:59.840 align:middle line:90%
I guess I am.

00:00:59.840 --> 00:01:00.665 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Now it follows you.

00:01:00.665 --> 00:01:02.720 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Yeah, now it
follows wherever I go.

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.519 align:middle line:84%
And friends of mine
say, are you going

00:01:04.519 --> 00:01:08.730 align:middle line:84%
to talk about this life,
or just the afterlife?

00:01:08.730 --> 00:01:10.010 align:middle line:90%
But people are fascinated.

00:01:10.010 --> 00:01:13.444 align:middle line:84%
Because, of course, what's going
to happen after we're here?

00:01:13.444 --> 00:01:15.860 align:middle line:84%
And what I've found, and what's
really fascinating in this

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:18.318 align:middle line:84%
research-- and I've been filming
people under deep hypnosis

00:01:18.318 --> 00:01:21.620 align:middle line:84%
for 10 years, and interviewing
people who've had near-death

00:01:21.620 --> 00:01:26.000 align:middle line:84%
experiences, and then most
recently, talking to mediums,

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:29.570 align:middle line:84%
who have access to people
on the other side--

00:01:29.570 --> 00:01:33.050 align:middle line:84%
and the idea is, in
mediumship, most mediums

00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:35.686 align:middle line:84%
they help you find
your love of your life.

00:01:35.686 --> 00:01:36.810 align:middle line:90%
Or they predict the future.

00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:37.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: In my case, I
was interested in comparing

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:41.040 align:middle line:90%
the research.

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:44.300 align:middle line:84%
So if you can access
somebody on the other side,

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:46.010 align:middle line:84%
would they be telling
me the same story

00:01:46.010 --> 00:01:48.270 align:middle line:84%
that people under deep
hypnosis are telling me?

00:01:48.270 --> 00:01:49.890 align:middle line:90%
And I found that to be the case.

00:01:49.890 --> 00:01:53.690 align:middle line:84%
So what I do when I interview
someone on the other side,

00:01:53.690 --> 00:01:56.689 align:middle line:84%
let's say, I'm not
interested in proving

00:01:56.689 --> 00:01:57.980 align:middle line:90%
that they're on the other side.

00:01:57.980 --> 00:02:00.060 align:middle line:84%
Because I've already done
that as many times as I--

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:00.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You believe
that from the get go.

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:01.880 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Yeah.

00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:04.040 align:middle line:84%
It's like when you
have an experience,

00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:07.130 align:middle line:84%
you no longer think of it
as something you don't know.

00:02:07.130 --> 00:02:08.139 align:middle line:90%
You know it.

00:02:08.139 --> 00:02:10.699 align:middle line:84%
So I've had the experience
of people on the other side

00:02:10.699 --> 00:02:12.060 align:middle line:90%
proving who they were to me.

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:14.060 align:middle line:84%
So in this case, what I
do is I interview people

00:02:14.060 --> 00:02:16.610 align:middle line:84%
on the other side
about their experience.

00:02:16.610 --> 00:02:19.130 align:middle line:84%
Who was there to greet
you when you crossed over?

00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:21.920 align:middle line:84%
What's it like for you
while you're over there?

00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:23.990 align:middle line:84%
What's it like for
you to talk to me?

00:02:23.990 --> 00:02:25.747 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And why
do they come back?

00:02:25.747 --> 00:02:27.830 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well, in general,
what they're trying--

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:31.190 align:middle line:84%
what they tell me is that
they have never left.

00:02:31.190 --> 00:02:32.900 align:middle line:84%
It's not-- it's
sort of like when

00:02:32.900 --> 00:02:35.300 align:middle line:84%
you step outside of
your body, you're

00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:36.560 align:middle line:90%
in a different frequency.

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:37.360 align:middle line:90%
The way--

00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:38.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But you go back.

00:02:38.690 --> 00:02:41.210 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well, you do
go back home, let's say.

00:02:41.210 --> 00:02:43.760 align:middle line:84%
And you go back, and
reconnect with the other 2/3

00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:46.130 align:middle line:84%
of your conscious energy
that's already back there.

00:02:46.130 --> 00:02:47.630 align:middle line:84%
This is what was
in the research,

00:02:47.630 --> 00:02:49.690 align:middle line:90%
and I found to be true.

00:02:49.690 --> 00:02:50.960 align:middle line:90%
But you can come back here.

00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:55.580 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, if you think of some
loved one, or say their name,

00:02:55.580 --> 00:02:56.682 align:middle line:90%
it's like a cell phone.

00:02:56.682 --> 00:02:58.640 align:middle line:84%
It's like pick up on a
cell phone, and dialing.

00:02:58.640 --> 00:02:59.900 align:middle line:84%
We don't know how
a cell phone works,

00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:00.860 align:middle line:90%
but you dial those numbers.

00:03:00.860 --> 00:03:01.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it finds them.

00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:02.918 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: And it finds them.

00:03:02.918 --> 00:03:05.527 align:middle line:90%
And if they're not busy--

00:03:05.527 --> 00:03:06.860 align:middle line:90%
you might get a message machine.

00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How could they
be busy in the afterlife?

00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:09.180 align:middle line:90%
What'd they do?

00:03:09.180 --> 00:03:11.360 align:middle line:90%
They sit on a cloud all day.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:12.650 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Playing that harp.

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:15.920 align:middle line:84%
Or like Prince, playing
with Jimi Hendrix.

00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:17.697 align:middle line:90%
No, actually.

00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:20.030 align:middle line:84%
What people report-- and I
can only tell you what people

00:03:20.030 --> 00:03:21.050 align:middle line:90%
report--

00:03:21.050 --> 00:03:23.960 align:middle line:84%
is that there's a
lot to do back there.

00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:26.030 align:middle line:84%
There's classrooms
that we go to.

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:27.150 align:middle line:90%
I visited some of them.

00:03:27.150 --> 00:03:27.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You have?

00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:30.004 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: While I was
under deep hypnosis, yes.

00:03:30.004 --> 00:03:31.670 align:middle line:84%
I'll just tell you
where that came from.

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:34.820 align:middle line:84%
My friend Luana Anders, when
she passed away in 1996--

00:03:34.820 --> 00:03:37.100 align:middle line:84%
she was a pretty
famous actress--

00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:39.680 align:middle line:84%
she was telling me,
before she died,

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:43.152 align:middle line:84%
I have this recurring dream
that I'm in a classroom.

00:03:43.152 --> 00:03:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And people are talking
about spirituality

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:46.443 align:middle line:84%
in a language I've
never heard before.

00:03:46.443 --> 00:03:48.470 align:middle line:84%
But somehow I
completely understand.

00:03:48.470 --> 00:03:51.266 align:middle line:84%
The day she died, her close
friend called me and said,

00:03:51.266 --> 00:03:53.390 align:middle line:84%
"I had this wonderful dream
about Luana last night.

00:03:53.390 --> 00:03:55.490 align:middle line:90%
She was in a classroom.

00:03:55.490 --> 00:03:56.840 align:middle line:90%
Everyone was dressed in white."

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:57.840 align:middle line:90%
And I said, "Oh my gosh.

00:03:57.840 --> 00:03:59.300 align:middle line:90%
That was her dream."

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:01.040 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned it to
her hospice care

00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:02.840 align:middle line:84%
nurse, who nearly
fainted, and said

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:05.840 align:middle line:90%
that was her recurring dream.

00:04:05.840 --> 00:04:07.430 align:middle line:90%
At first, it was startling.

00:04:07.430 --> 00:04:09.530 align:middle line:90%
I went to class for 18 years.

00:04:09.530 --> 00:04:12.260 align:middle line:84%
Do I really want to go back
to class in the afterlife?

00:04:12.260 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:84%
And then, when I picked
up Michael Newton's book,

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:17.060 align:middle line:84%
"Journey of Souls," there
in the first chapter

00:04:17.060 --> 00:04:20.190 align:middle line:84%
was a guy saying that while
he was under deep hypnosis,

00:04:20.190 --> 00:04:22.050 align:middle line:90%
he was visiting a classroom.

00:04:22.050 --> 00:04:25.290 align:middle line:84%
So that's what impelled me
in starting this research.

00:04:25.290 --> 00:04:29.259 align:middle line:84%
So when I finally did
a between-life session,

00:04:29.259 --> 00:04:30.800 align:middle line:84%
they said, "Where
do you want to go?"

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:33.680 align:middle line:84%
And I said, "I want to
go visit my friends."

00:04:33.680 --> 00:04:35.330 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself
in a classroom.

00:04:35.330 --> 00:04:37.850 align:middle line:90%
Not hers, but another classroom.

00:04:37.850 --> 00:04:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And I was there with a
teacher and students,

00:04:40.520 --> 00:04:44.060 align:middle line:84%
who were all looking at me
like I was their oldest friend.

00:04:44.060 --> 00:04:45.740 align:middle line:84%
People I've never
seen before, but they

00:04:45.740 --> 00:04:49.320 align:middle line:84%
were looking at me like it was
important for me to be there.

00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:51.490 align:middle line:84%
But then, after
that class, I went

00:04:51.490 --> 00:04:53.240 align:middle line:84%
to-- they said, "Where
do you want to go?"

00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:55.100 align:middle line:84%
I said, "I want to
go visit Luana."

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm in this
classroom, a giant auditorium.

00:04:57.980 --> 00:05:00.170 align:middle line:84%
I can see a teacher
in the front.

00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:02.120 align:middle line:90%
And she's--

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:03.607 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: All in
white robes, right?

00:05:03.607 --> 00:05:05.940 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well, in this case,
I didn't see white robes.

00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:08.030 align:middle line:84%
So that might have
been the front row.

00:05:08.030 --> 00:05:10.010 align:middle line:84%
I just saw normal
people sitting around.

00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
And I started telling
the hypnotherapist,

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:15.330 align:middle line:84%
"I'm in a classroom
that deals with healing.

00:05:15.330 --> 00:05:18.140 align:middle line:84%
The students here learn
how to channel the healing

00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:19.550 align:middle line:90%
light of the universe.

00:05:19.550 --> 00:05:22.150 align:middle line:84%
So that when a doctor or
a healer on the planet

00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:25.210 align:middle line:84%
needs to heal somebody,
that's how they do it."

00:05:25.210 --> 00:05:29.630 align:middle line:84%
And a student turned to me,
in my mind's eye, and said,

00:05:29.630 --> 00:05:31.900 align:middle line:84%
"You don't know what
you're talking about."

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
"Well, this is odd.

00:05:34.090 --> 00:05:36.730 align:middle line:84%
Why would this student
be chastising me

00:05:36.730 --> 00:05:38.230 align:middle line:90%
if I was making it up?"

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:39.520 align:middle line:90%
But then I said, "Look.

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:42.340 align:middle line:84%
Not every doctor signs
up to cure everybody.

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:44.710 align:middle line:84%
Not every person
signs up to be cured."

00:05:44.710 --> 00:05:47.350 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes people want
to examine an illness,

00:05:47.350 --> 00:05:48.860 align:middle line:90%
the energy of an illness.

00:05:48.860 --> 00:05:50.560 align:middle line:90%
So not everybody gets cured."

00:05:50.560 --> 00:05:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And the students looked
at me, went, "OK.

00:05:53.230 --> 00:05:55.460 align:middle line:84%
I guess you do know what
you're talking about."

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:58.000 align:middle line:84%
I've been back to that
classroom many times.

00:05:58.000 --> 00:05:59.844 align:middle line:84%
I've done five
between-life sessions.

00:05:59.844 --> 00:06:00.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's a lot.

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:03.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: The second time
I went back to the class,

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:04.427 align:middle line:90%
it was as if--

00:06:04.427 --> 00:06:06.760 align:middle line:84%
it was two years later with
a different hypnotherapist--

00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:09.190 align:middle line:84%
but it was as if 20
minutes had gone by.

00:06:09.190 --> 00:06:11.740 align:middle line:84%
My friend Luana was
introducing me to the teacher

00:06:11.740 --> 00:06:13.570 align:middle line:90%
and apologizing.

00:06:13.570 --> 00:06:15.170 align:middle line:90%
And saying, "This is my friend.

00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:15.250 align:middle line:90%
He's--"

00:06:15.250 --> 00:06:16.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: In this hypnotic state?

00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:17.440 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Exactly.

00:06:17.440 --> 00:06:20.560 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, is
that it felt like it had

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:22.180 align:middle line:90%
happened 20 minutes earlier.

00:06:22.180 --> 00:06:23.860 align:middle line:90%
But it was two years.

00:06:23.860 --> 00:06:26.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Richard, how do we
know that the brain isn't doing

00:06:26.830 --> 00:06:30.070 align:middle line:84%
these things to us, either
at the moment of death,

00:06:30.070 --> 00:06:32.200 align:middle line:84%
or when you're close to
dying, or when you or

00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:34.220 align:middle line:90%
have a near-death experience?

00:06:34.220 --> 00:06:37.270 align:middle line:84%
How do we know that there's not
some quirk in the brain that

00:06:37.270 --> 00:06:40.130 align:middle line:90%
creates this light, this image?

00:06:40.130 --> 00:06:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And does it-- and that
it really doesn't exist?

00:06:42.730 --> 00:06:43.900 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Exactly.

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:47.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, what I focus on
is new information.

00:06:47.690 --> 00:06:49.540 align:middle line:84%
So that would
mean, let's say you

00:06:49.540 --> 00:06:53.110 align:middle line:84%
have a near-death experience,
and you see somebody.

00:06:53.110 --> 00:06:54.910 align:middle line:84%
And when you see
that person, you

00:06:54.910 --> 00:06:58.900 align:middle line:84%
learn something new from them
that you couldn't have known.

00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:01.870 align:middle line:84%
Like seeing a sister or
brother that you didn't know

00:07:01.870 --> 00:07:04.840 align:middle line:84%
existed, but had died
before you were born.

00:07:04.840 --> 00:07:07.600 align:middle line:84%
That's what happened
to Dr. Eben Alexander.

00:07:07.600 --> 00:07:10.380 align:middle line:84%
When he was there, he met a
woman who guided him around,

00:07:10.380 --> 00:07:11.180 align:middle line:90%
and he--

00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:12.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: "Proof of
Heaven," his book.

00:07:12.070 --> 00:07:13.278 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: "Proof of Heaven."

00:07:13.278 --> 00:07:16.430 align:middle line:84%
And what happened was, about
six months after his experience,

00:07:16.430 --> 00:07:19.570 align:middle line:84%
the family that had put
him up for adoption--

00:07:19.570 --> 00:07:21.070 align:middle line:90%
because he was an adoptee--

00:07:21.070 --> 00:07:24.080 align:middle line:84%
sent him a photograph of
a sister he'd never met.

00:07:24.080 --> 00:07:27.670 align:middle line:84%
And that was the woman who'd
guided him around that journey.

00:07:27.670 --> 00:07:32.420 align:middle line:84%
In the book "Heaven is for
Real" by Todd and Colton Burpo,

00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:33.220 align:middle line:90%
he found--

00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:35.650 align:middle line:84%
met a sister, who
he had never known.

00:07:35.650 --> 00:07:36.640 align:middle line:90%
But she had died.

00:07:36.640 --> 00:07:38.475 align:middle line:84%
So I focus on this
new information.

00:07:38.475 --> 00:07:40.767 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, and that's
pretty startling information.

00:07:40.767 --> 00:07:41.724 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: It is, yeah.

00:07:41.724 --> 00:07:44.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because out of nowhere,
how would an Eben Alexander

00:07:44.450 --> 00:07:46.320 align:middle line:90%
have known until he went across.

00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:48.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: But what I've
found in my research

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:51.380 align:middle line:84%
is that you can ask questions
to get new information.

00:07:51.380 --> 00:07:53.440 align:middle line:84%
So I was saying, I was
working with mediums.

00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:55.210 align:middle line:84%
So what I do is, I'm
interviewing somebody

00:07:55.210 --> 00:07:56.110 align:middle line:90%
on the other side.

00:07:56.110 --> 00:07:57.850 align:middle line:90%
And I'm asking them.

00:07:57.850 --> 00:08:00.190 align:middle line:84%
They give me a
piece of information

00:08:00.190 --> 00:08:02.620 align:middle line:84%
that I can now go to
their family, and say--

00:08:02.620 --> 00:08:05.050 align:middle line:84%
I only focus on people
that I knew, generally.

00:08:05.050 --> 00:08:07.260 align:middle line:84%
People I knew or
the medium knows.

00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:10.000 align:middle line:84%
And then I can ask people,
"Did you know this?"

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:11.170 align:middle line:90%
And they research it.

00:08:11.170 --> 00:08:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And find out, oh
my gosh, indeed.

00:08:13.690 --> 00:08:14.990 align:middle line:90%
I did not know that.

00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:16.270 align:middle line:90%
But I now I do.

00:08:16.270 --> 00:08:17.710 align:middle line:84%
Because you've
just told it to me.

00:08:17.710 --> 00:08:20.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were you friends with
the late actor Bill Paxton?

00:08:20.260 --> 00:08:21.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: I was.

00:08:21.060 --> 00:08:23.710 align:middle line:10%
Billy and I started off
our careers together.

00:08:23.710 --> 00:08:25.694 align:middle line:10%
His took off in one direction.

00:08:25.694 --> 00:08:26.610 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: So did yours.

00:08:26.610 --> 00:08:27.460 align:middle line:10%
So did yours.

00:08:27.460 --> 00:08:28.940 align:middle line:10%
>>MARTINI: Mine went off
in a different direction.

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:29.740 align:middle line:10%
It's OK.

00:08:29.740 --> 00:08:32.530 align:middle line:10%
We used to razz each
other, constantly.

00:08:32.530 --> 00:08:33.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Great actor.

00:08:33.470 --> 00:08:35.261 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Great actor
and a wonderful guy.

00:08:35.261 --> 00:08:38.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Died tragically, I
think, in a hospital room.

00:08:38.010 --> 00:08:39.260 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: In a hospital room.

00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:42.970 align:middle line:84%
He had a lifelong
condition for his heart.

00:08:42.970 --> 00:08:44.890 align:middle line:84%
And they were trying to
fix it and repair it.

00:08:44.890 --> 00:08:45.605 align:middle line:90%
And apparently--

00:08:45.605 --> 00:08:46.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Something happened.

00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:47.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: --things went--
something went wrong.

00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:48.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But you dealt
with a medium, right?

00:08:48.630 --> 00:08:50.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: But well,
in Bill's case,

00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:53.620 align:middle line:84%
I'd known him since we
started off together.

00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:55.390 align:middle line:84%
And he was going to
star in my first film.

00:08:55.390 --> 00:08:56.470 align:middle line:90%
And so we were close friends.

00:08:56.470 --> 00:08:58.100 align:middle line:84%
And he helped me
rewrite some things.

00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And over the years, we
always stayed in touch.

00:09:00.250 --> 00:09:03.536 align:middle line:84%
And when he passed
away, I had meetings

00:09:03.536 --> 00:09:04.660 align:middle line:90%
with two different mediums.

00:09:04.660 --> 00:09:06.386 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, "Well,
let's just see."

00:09:06.386 --> 00:09:08.260 align:middle line:84%
But in this case, instead
of saying his name,

00:09:08.260 --> 00:09:10.930 align:middle line:84%
I just said, "I have
a friend named Bill

00:09:10.930 --> 00:09:12.550 align:middle line:90%
that I'd like to talk to."

00:09:12.550 --> 00:09:14.200 align:middle line:90%
And in both cases--

00:09:14.200 --> 00:09:16.780 align:middle line:84%
Jennifer Shaffer and
Kimberly Babcock--

00:09:16.780 --> 00:09:18.010 align:middle line:90%
they don't know each other.

00:09:18.010 --> 00:09:21.100 align:middle line:84%
But in both cases, Bill
came through very clearly.

00:09:21.100 --> 00:09:22.930 align:middle line:90%
He talked to Jennifer.

00:09:22.930 --> 00:09:25.506 align:middle line:84%
She said to me, "Why is he
showing me the Titanic?"

00:09:25.506 --> 00:09:27.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's take a look at
Jennifer Shaffer right now.

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: OK.

00:09:28.270 --> 00:09:29.379 align:middle line:90%
Very good.

00:09:29.379 --> 00:09:33.510 align:middle line:84%
We have a mutual friend who
passed away recently, Bill.

00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:36.052 align:middle line:10%
And is he avail-- does
he want to talk to us?

00:09:36.052 --> 00:09:37.760 align:middle line:10%
>>JENNIFER SHAFFER:
Oh, they just danced.

00:09:37.760 --> 00:09:39.100 align:middle line:10%
That's interesting.

00:09:39.100 --> 00:09:40.043 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Who's they?

00:09:40.043 --> 00:09:41.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SHAFFER: Bill.

00:09:41.010 --> 00:09:41.820 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: And?

00:09:41.820 --> 00:09:42.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SHAFFER: Luana.

00:09:42.780 --> 00:09:44.747 align:middle line:90%
They did a little tango thing.

00:09:44.747 --> 00:09:45.674 align:middle line:90%
It was kind of funny.

00:09:45.674 --> 00:09:47.340 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Does Bill
want to talk to us?

00:09:47.340 --> 00:09:50.060 align:middle line:90%


00:09:50.060 --> 00:09:51.810 align:middle line:84%
>>SHAFFER: He just
filed his nails.

00:09:51.810 --> 00:09:53.220 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what he just did.

00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:55.480 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: That means,
"Yeah, I'm here.

00:09:55.480 --> 00:09:56.460 align:middle line:90%
Whatever."

00:09:56.460 --> 00:09:58.120 align:middle line:90%
>>SHAFFER: Whatever.

00:09:58.120 --> 00:09:58.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:09:58.920 --> 00:09:59.820 align:middle line:90%
Shampooing his hair.

00:09:59.820 --> 00:10:00.620 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:00.620 --> 00:10:01.420 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Yes.

00:10:01.420 --> 00:10:03.920 align:middle line:84%
Get ready for your
close up, Bill.

00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:05.080 align:middle line:90%
Make up.

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:08.190 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to
need a lot of it.

00:10:08.190 --> 00:10:10.420 align:middle line:84%
So tell us what it's
like for you over there.

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:12.474 align:middle line:90%
And who was the first person--

00:10:12.474 --> 00:10:13.640 align:middle line:90%
>>SHAFFER: He says it's fun.

00:10:13.640 --> 00:10:15.680 align:middle line:90%
He's scaring people.

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:18.150 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Who was the first
person to greet you when you

00:10:18.150 --> 00:10:18.800 align:middle line:90%
stepped off--

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:19.230 align:middle line:90%
>>SHAFFER: His dad.

00:10:19.230 --> 00:10:19.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: His dad.

00:10:19.850 --> 00:10:20.750 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:20.750 --> 00:10:24.510 align:middle line:84%
And was that a happy
thing, a happy connection?

00:10:24.510 --> 00:10:27.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SHAFFER: Shocking,
because that meant he died.

00:10:27.290 --> 00:10:29.664 align:middle line:90%
So I just saw that--

00:10:29.664 --> 00:10:30.660 align:middle line:90%
Hold on.

00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:32.302 align:middle line:90%
It's interpretation.

00:10:32.302 --> 00:10:33.640 align:middle line:90%
He said, "Yes, at first.

00:10:33.640 --> 00:10:36.190 align:middle line:90%
That subsided."

00:10:36.190 --> 00:10:42.940 align:middle line:84%
So Billy's saying that
at first he was startled.

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:45.760 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't scary, like
his heart-- it wasn't scary.

00:10:45.760 --> 00:10:49.930 align:middle line:90%


00:10:49.930 --> 00:10:53.730 align:middle line:84%
He says it was recognition
of both worlds,

00:10:53.730 --> 00:10:55.250 align:middle line:90%
that he's leaving one.

00:10:55.250 --> 00:10:57.640 align:middle line:84%
But he shows them going
in together, as one.

00:10:57.640 --> 00:10:59.480 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Was this
an exit point for you?

00:10:59.480 --> 00:11:01.410 align:middle line:84%
Was this something
that you had planned

00:11:01.410 --> 00:11:03.604 align:middle line:90%
that maybe would happen?

00:11:03.604 --> 00:11:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Was this the right time,
or was this the wrong time?

00:11:05.770 --> 00:11:13.370 align:middle line:90%


00:11:13.370 --> 00:11:15.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SHAFFER: His
physical body was--

00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:19.182 align:middle line:84%
it was the wrong
time for him here.

00:11:19.182 --> 00:11:21.960 align:middle line:84%
It was the right
time for his soul.

00:11:21.960 --> 00:11:23.275 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: I understand.

00:11:23.275 --> 00:11:24.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:25.764 align:middle line:90%
What'd you learn from that?

00:11:25.764 --> 00:11:27.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well,
it's interesting.

00:11:27.180 --> 00:11:30.480 align:middle line:84%
When you hear someone tell you
something from the other side,

00:11:30.480 --> 00:11:32.040 align:middle line:90%
all you can do is take notes.

00:11:32.040 --> 00:11:34.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think you were
really talking to Bill Paxton

00:11:34.540 --> 00:11:34.770 align:middle line:90%
through her?

00:11:34.770 --> 00:11:37.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well, once we started
talking about the Titanic--

00:11:37.620 --> 00:11:39.540 align:middle line:84%
she said, "Why is he
showing me the Titanic?

00:11:39.540 --> 00:11:42.300 align:middle line:84%
Is this the Bill that was
in the movie "The Titanic?"

00:11:42.300 --> 00:11:44.010 align:middle line:84%
And I said, "Why
don't you ask him?"

00:11:44.010 --> 00:11:47.250 align:middle line:84%
So ultimately, we went
through a number of things--

00:11:47.250 --> 00:11:49.200 align:middle line:84%
what I would consider
to be hallmarks--

00:11:49.200 --> 00:11:51.541 align:middle line:84%
where I knew that only Bill
would know the answers.

00:11:51.541 --> 00:11:52.341 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You knew.

00:11:52.341 --> 00:11:52.880 align:middle line:90%
Bill knew.

00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:53.430 align:middle line:90%
She didn't.

00:11:53.430 --> 00:11:54.230 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Correct.

00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:55.090 align:middle line:90%
That she did not.

00:11:55.090 --> 00:11:57.810 align:middle line:84%
But I also spoke
with another medium.

00:11:57.810 --> 00:12:00.060 align:middle line:84%
And she said the
same thing about who

00:12:00.060 --> 00:12:02.140 align:middle line:90%
met you when you crossed over.

00:12:02.140 --> 00:12:04.560 align:middle line:84%
So when you compare
the two mediums saying

00:12:04.560 --> 00:12:07.260 align:middle line:84%
the identical things,
then you at least

00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:08.619 align:middle line:90%
have a data set that you could--

00:12:08.619 --> 00:12:10.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And one didn't know
what the other was saying.

00:12:10.910 --> 00:12:11.826 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Not at all.

00:12:11.826 --> 00:12:14.040 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, in the second
one, she didn't know who--

00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:16.440 align:middle line:90%
he wouldn't tell her who he was.

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:18.180 align:middle line:84%
And at the very
end, I said, "Billy,

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:19.710 align:middle line:90%
show-- tell her who you are."

00:12:19.710 --> 00:12:21.300 align:middle line:90%
And he did this, she said.

00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:22.290 align:middle line:90%
And did that.

00:12:22.290 --> 00:12:24.330 align:middle line:84%
And then her father
called on the phone.

00:12:24.330 --> 00:12:26.384 align:middle line:84%
This medium's
father on the phone.

00:12:26.384 --> 00:12:28.050 align:middle line:84%
And she said, "What
are you doing, Dad?"

00:12:28.050 --> 00:12:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And she said, "I'm watching this
movie with Bill Paxton called

00:12:31.170 --> 00:12:32.402 align:middle line:90%
"Twister."

00:12:32.402 --> 00:12:33.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Synchronicity.

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:35.170 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: What are
the odds of that?

00:12:35.170 --> 00:12:37.020 align:middle line:84%
But at the same
time, I'm not trying

00:12:37.020 --> 00:12:40.410 align:middle line:84%
to prove something that I
can feel that I already know.

00:12:40.410 --> 00:12:44.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You have touched a lot
of lives in your own career.

00:12:44.630 --> 00:12:48.650 align:middle line:84%
But what has your research
into the afterlife

00:12:48.650 --> 00:12:51.140 align:middle line:90%
taught you about what this is?

00:12:51.140 --> 00:12:54.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well, some
basic fundamental things.

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:57.470 align:middle line:84%
Which is, I think
of a caterpillar.

00:12:57.470 --> 00:12:59.355 align:middle line:84%
And what does the
caterpillar turn into it?

00:12:59.355 --> 00:13:00.155 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It morphs.

00:13:00.155 --> 00:13:02.690 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: It morphs
into a butterfly.

00:13:02.690 --> 00:13:05.430 align:middle line:90%
And do we mourn the cocoon?

00:13:05.430 --> 00:13:06.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:13:06.230 --> 00:13:09.020 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Do we do we have
a parade for the cocoon?

00:13:09.020 --> 00:13:11.270 align:middle line:90%
Do we put up a shrine for the--

00:13:11.270 --> 00:13:12.350 align:middle line:90%
well, we kind of do.

00:13:12.350 --> 00:13:14.516 align:middle line:84%
We do these things with
people who have passed away.

00:13:14.516 --> 00:13:15.542 align:middle line:90%
We look at the cocoon.

00:13:15.542 --> 00:13:17.000 align:middle line:84%
And we spent a lot
of time working.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:20.130 align:middle line:84%
But we don't even think
about the butterfly,

00:13:20.130 --> 00:13:22.220 align:middle line:90%
which is having an adventure.

00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:25.112 align:middle line:84%
And what a wonderful thing,
when you start to realize--

00:13:25.112 --> 00:13:26.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting analogy.

00:13:26.320 --> 00:13:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: --it's all part of
the journey that we're all on.

00:13:30.030 --> 00:13:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And if we can focus a little
bit on the butterfly, then

00:13:33.170 --> 00:13:35.480 align:middle line:84%
maybe we can understand
that the things

00:13:35.480 --> 00:13:38.900 align:middle line:84%
that we consider to be really
upsetting, or stressful,

00:13:38.900 --> 00:13:42.500 align:middle line:84%
or painful, are just part
of that cocoon's journey.

00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:45.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You've had
friends that are atheists.

00:13:45.270 --> 00:13:47.104 align:middle line:90%
And they've died.

00:13:47.104 --> 00:13:48.020 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: It happens.

00:13:48.020 --> 00:13:49.145 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Have they changed?

00:13:49.145 --> 00:13:52.370 align:middle line:84%
Have they come back to you
and said, "Whoa, Rich, I

00:13:52.370 --> 00:13:53.980 align:middle line:90%
was way off on this."

00:13:53.980 --> 00:13:55.480 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Yes, as
a matter of fact.

00:13:55.480 --> 00:13:57.260 align:middle line:90%
It's funny you mentioned that.

00:13:57.260 --> 00:13:59.870 align:middle line:10%
A friend of mine, Harry
Dean Stanton, an actor,

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:02.730 align:middle line:10%
who passed away a
couple of months ago--

00:14:02.730 --> 00:14:04.430 align:middle line:10%
but he was also
very close friends

00:14:04.430 --> 00:14:06.800 align:middle line:10%
with Luana, Luana Anders.

00:14:06.800 --> 00:14:11.060 align:middle line:84%
I worked with Luana to help me
gather these people together.

00:14:11.060 --> 00:14:12.190 align:middle line:90%
Because I know her.

00:14:12.190 --> 00:14:13.710 align:middle line:90%
I know her frequency.

00:14:13.710 --> 00:14:16.697 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, and in this case Harry
Dean, who was a famous atheist,

00:14:16.697 --> 00:14:19.280 align:middle line:84%
and he just made a movie called
"Lucky," where he talks about,

00:14:19.280 --> 00:14:21.050 align:middle line:90%
there is no afterlife.

00:14:21.050 --> 00:14:23.240 align:middle line:84%
He was also in "Big
Love" with Bill Paxton.

00:14:23.240 --> 00:14:24.920 align:middle line:10%
So there's a connection there.

00:14:24.920 --> 00:14:26.030 align:middle line:10%
But Harry came through.

00:14:26.030 --> 00:14:28.130 align:middle line:10%
And I said, "So
Harry, what was it

00:14:28.130 --> 00:14:31.880 align:middle line:10%
like when you realized
there was an afterlife?"

00:14:31.880 --> 00:14:34.250 align:middle line:90%
And he said, "Luana tricked me."

00:14:34.250 --> 00:14:35.180 align:middle line:90%
And I said, "How?"

00:14:35.180 --> 00:14:37.520 align:middle line:84%
And then, he gave me
this elaborate story

00:14:37.520 --> 00:14:40.730 align:middle line:84%
of how she had started
appearing at his hospital bed

00:14:40.730 --> 00:14:41.826 align:middle line:90%
as he was dying.

00:14:41.826 --> 00:14:43.700 align:middle line:84%
And he thought, "Oh,
this is a hallucination.

00:14:43.700 --> 00:14:46.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm just-- my brain
is hallucinating."

00:14:46.490 --> 00:14:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And then, when he crossed
over, he was in a car with her.

00:14:50.270 --> 00:14:52.940 align:middle line:84%
But it was 1967, and
they're on their way

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:55.460 align:middle line:90%
to the Monterey Pop Festival.

00:14:55.460 --> 00:14:59.300 align:middle line:84%
This is Jennifer telling
me this, from Harry.

00:14:59.300 --> 00:15:00.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm the only person
in the room who

00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:03.290 align:middle line:84%
knows that Harry was
driving the car when they

00:15:03.290 --> 00:15:05.240 align:middle line:90%
went to the Monterey Festival.

00:15:05.240 --> 00:15:06.980 align:middle line:84%
But now, she then
proceeds to say

00:15:06.980 --> 00:15:09.060 align:middle line:84%
who is in the car,
where they went,

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:10.310 align:middle line:90%
who they went to see on stage.

00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:10.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And she knew it all?

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:11.975 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: She knew it all.

00:15:11.975 --> 00:15:15.350 align:middle line:84%
Jimi Hendrix, all these details
that Jennifer could never

00:15:15.350 --> 00:15:16.320 align:middle line:90%
have known.

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:19.220 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, "So at what
point did you realize?"

00:15:19.220 --> 00:15:21.020 align:middle line:90%
He said, "We got a flat tire."

00:15:21.020 --> 00:15:22.640 align:middle line:84%
He said, "I thought
when you die,

00:15:22.640 --> 00:15:24.220 align:middle line:84%
you turn-- you
fall into a dream.

00:15:24.220 --> 00:15:25.220 align:middle line:90%
You're in a happy dream.

00:15:25.220 --> 00:15:27.376 align:middle line:84%
And that's your
reality forever."

00:15:27.376 --> 00:15:29.000 align:middle line:84%
He said, "But then
we got a flat tire."

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.005 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In the--
on the other side?

00:15:30.005 --> 00:15:30.575 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: In the dream.

00:15:30.575 --> 00:15:31.602 align:middle line:90%
On the other side.

00:15:31.602 --> 00:15:33.560 align:middle line:84%
And I got out-- he said,
"I got out of the car.

00:15:33.560 --> 00:15:34.476 align:middle line:90%
And I looked at Luana.

00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.020 align:middle line:90%
And I said, wait a minute.

00:15:36.020 --> 00:15:37.670 align:middle line:90%
We didn't have a flat tire.

00:15:37.670 --> 00:15:40.370 align:middle line:90%
And she said, I know."

00:15:40.370 --> 00:15:43.700 align:middle line:84%
And he said, "It was that moment
I realized she had given me

00:15:43.700 --> 00:15:45.590 align:middle line:90%
a soft landing."

00:15:45.590 --> 00:15:46.970 align:middle line:90%
That was his words.

00:15:46.970 --> 00:15:50.660 align:middle line:84%
Now, he also described to me
the deathbed scene, where there

00:15:50.660 --> 00:15:52.490 align:middle line:90%
were five women around him.

00:15:52.490 --> 00:15:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And he said, "And I
saw a baby that I was

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:56.900 align:middle line:90%
supposed to have back in 1962.

00:15:56.900 --> 00:15:58.490 align:middle line:90%
The baby had died."

00:15:58.490 --> 00:16:00.770 align:middle line:84%
He said, "But I was
there holding the baby."

00:16:00.770 --> 00:16:03.290 align:middle line:84%
Now, when I went to his
memorial service a week later,

00:16:03.290 --> 00:16:06.770 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Does anybody know
anything about how Harry died?"

00:16:06.770 --> 00:16:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And this woman told me there
were five women around him.

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:14.467 align:middle line:84%
And he asked out loud,
"Somebody hand me the baby."

00:16:14.467 --> 00:16:15.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: At the moment of death?

00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:17.460 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: At the
moment of death.

00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:18.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Weird.

00:16:18.260 --> 00:16:19.550 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: I said to
Harry, "What do you

00:16:19.550 --> 00:16:20.674 align:middle line:90%
want to tell your friends?"

00:16:20.674 --> 00:16:21.920 align:middle line:90%
And I mean, his friends--

00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:24.950 align:middle line:84%
Nicholson, and Al Pacino,
and Warren Beatty--

00:16:24.950 --> 00:16:26.720 align:middle line:84%
they were all at the
memorial service.

00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:28.386 align:middle line:84%
I said, "What do you
want to tell them?"

00:16:28.386 --> 00:16:30.860 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Tell them
there is an afterlife."

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:33.230 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Harry, nobody's
going to believe

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:36.154 align:middle line:84%
that Richard was talking
to you on the flipside--"

00:16:36.154 --> 00:16:37.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And goes up
to them, and says--

00:16:37.820 --> 00:16:38.370 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: And right.

00:16:38.370 --> 00:16:39.786 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
go, you're nutty.

00:16:39.786 --> 00:16:41.510 align:middle line:90%
So he said, "All right.

00:16:41.510 --> 00:16:45.500 align:middle line:84%
Tell them to believe in the
possibility of an afterlife.

00:16:45.500 --> 00:16:47.990 align:middle line:84%
Because then they won't
waste their lives, like I

00:16:47.990 --> 00:16:49.520 align:middle line:90%
did, arguing--"

00:16:49.520 --> 00:16:50.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That it didn't exist.

00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: "--that
it didn't exist."

00:16:51.500 --> 00:16:53.840 align:middle line:84%
He said it was like
being on a treadmill.

00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And I said, "So why did
you come to believe that?"

00:16:56.060 --> 00:16:58.080 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Too many
friends of mine had died.

00:16:58.080 --> 00:17:01.070 align:middle line:84%
I had to wall myself
off from that emotion."

00:17:01.070 --> 00:17:03.890 align:middle line:84%
And now, when I talked to
him-- because he shows up.

00:17:03.890 --> 00:17:06.480 align:middle line:84%
Jennifer and I do this every
week, have these sessions.

00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:07.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Your sessions.

00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:09.046 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: He shows up,
and says, "Thank you."

00:17:09.046 --> 00:17:10.730 align:middle line:90%
And I say, "Thank me for what?"

00:17:10.730 --> 00:17:15.319 align:middle line:84%
He says, "For throwing a lot
of dust in to people's world."

00:17:15.319 --> 00:17:18.890 align:middle line:84%
Because now they know that
the things that I said-- he

00:17:18.890 --> 00:17:22.040 align:middle line:84%
told one of his friends,
the medication you're taking

00:17:22.040 --> 00:17:23.069 align:middle line:90%
is drying you up.

00:17:23.069 --> 00:17:25.250 align:middle line:90%
You need to drink more water.

00:17:25.250 --> 00:17:26.990 align:middle line:90%
Very obscure detail.

00:17:26.990 --> 00:17:29.370 align:middle line:84%
But his son came
up to me and said,

00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:30.590 align:middle line:90%
"We tell him that every day.

00:17:30.590 --> 00:17:33.710 align:middle line:84%
How could you
possibly know that?"

00:17:33.710 --> 00:17:34.849 align:middle line:90%
So listen.

00:17:34.849 --> 00:17:36.890 align:middle line:84%
You want to talk to your
friends on the flipside?

00:17:36.890 --> 00:17:38.660 align:middle line:90%
You can.

00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:40.500 align:middle line:84%
Your loved ones, the
ones you've lost.

00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:41.300 align:middle line:90%
You can.

00:17:41.300 --> 00:17:43.660 align:middle line:90%
There's a method for doing it.

00:17:43.660 --> 00:17:44.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I believe that.

00:17:44.660 --> 00:17:47.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: And so I can
tell you, in one case, we--

00:17:47.610 --> 00:17:49.360 align:middle line:84%
Jennifer and I were
having a conversation.

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:50.807 align:middle line:90%
And Michael Newton showed up.

00:17:50.807 --> 00:17:51.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The doctor?

00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:52.630 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: The doctor.

00:17:52.630 --> 00:17:54.770 align:middle line:84%
And Michael and I were
not close friends.

00:17:54.770 --> 00:17:57.880 align:middle line:84%
So like I said, mostly
it's people I knew.

00:17:57.880 --> 00:17:59.740 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I'd interviewed him.

00:17:59.740 --> 00:18:00.540 align:middle line:90%
And we emailed.

00:18:00.540 --> 00:18:02.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he was
a renowned doctor.

00:18:02.110 --> 00:18:03.155 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Renowned
psychologist.

00:18:03.155 --> 00:18:03.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Dealing
with the afterlife.

00:18:03.930 --> 00:18:06.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Michael Newton,
who wrote all those books.

00:18:06.310 --> 00:18:08.320 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, I said to
Michael, "What are you

00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:09.790 align:middle line:90%
doing over there?"

00:18:09.790 --> 00:18:13.377 align:middle line:84%
He said, "I'm doing noetic
science from this side."

00:18:13.377 --> 00:18:14.960 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what
noetic science was.

00:18:14.960 --> 00:18:15.595 align:middle line:90%
Neither did Jennifer.

00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:15.850 align:middle line:90%
I had to look it up.

00:18:15.850 --> 00:18:17.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Edgar Mitchell did.

00:18:17.270 --> 00:18:18.790 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Edgar Mitchell did.

00:18:18.790 --> 00:18:19.810 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't.

00:18:19.810 --> 00:18:21.160 align:middle line:90%
And so now, I said, "All right.

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:24.400 align:middle line:84%
So what-- how--
give me a 1, 2, 3.

00:18:24.400 --> 00:18:27.790 align:middle line:84%
How do we tell people to reach
to the people on that side?"

00:18:27.790 --> 00:18:30.610 align:middle line:90%
And he said, "Say their name."

00:18:30.610 --> 00:18:32.590 align:middle line:84%
I said, "In your
mind, or out loud?"

00:18:32.590 --> 00:18:34.060 align:middle line:90%
He said, "It doesn't matter."

00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:35.650 align:middle line:90%
I said, "OK."

00:18:35.650 --> 00:18:37.360 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Make a
list of questions you

00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:39.130 align:middle line:90%
want to ask your loved one."

00:18:39.130 --> 00:18:40.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All right.

00:18:40.420 --> 00:18:41.795 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: And I
said, "Well, how

00:18:41.795 --> 00:18:43.900 align:middle line:84%
do people know that
they're not making it up

00:18:43.900 --> 00:18:45.160 align:middle line:90%
when they hear something?"

00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:47.380 align:middle line:84%
He said, "When they
answer the question before

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:49.210 align:middle line:90%
you can form it."

00:18:49.210 --> 00:18:51.384 align:middle line:84%
Then you'll know
you're connected.

00:18:51.384 --> 00:18:53.050 align:middle line:84%
So you have a list
of questions that you

00:18:53.050 --> 00:18:54.520 align:middle line:90%
don't know the answer to.

00:18:54.520 --> 00:18:56.440 align:middle line:90%
You start to ask this question.

00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:57.476 align:middle line:90%
And it's answered.

00:18:57.476 --> 00:18:59.725 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So I got to tell
you this great story of Rose

00:18:59.725 --> 00:19:00.525 align:middle line:90%
and Betty.

00:19:00.525 --> 00:19:03.190 align:middle line:84%
They were friends
since childhood, Rich.

00:19:03.190 --> 00:19:05.710 align:middle line:84%
And as they got into
their later lives,

00:19:05.710 --> 00:19:07.310 align:middle line:90%
they decided to cut a pack.

00:19:07.310 --> 00:19:08.110 align:middle line:90%
They wanted a deal.

00:19:08.110 --> 00:19:12.370 align:middle line:84%
And that was, whichever
died and went first,

00:19:12.370 --> 00:19:14.410 align:middle line:84%
the other would come
back and tell the living

00:19:14.410 --> 00:19:16.180 align:middle line:90%
one what it was like.

00:19:16.180 --> 00:19:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And they did all kinds of things
together in their real life.

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:20.660 align:middle line:90%
They played softball together.

00:19:20.660 --> 00:19:22.100 align:middle line:90%
They went to the prom together.

00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:23.980 align:middle line:90%
They went to college together.

00:19:23.980 --> 00:19:26.500 align:middle line:90%
And one day Betty died.

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:29.290 align:middle line:90%
And it was a sad thing for Rose.

00:19:29.290 --> 00:19:31.720 align:middle line:90%
And Rose is in bed one night.

00:19:31.720 --> 00:19:35.320 align:middle line:84%
And she hears--
she gets woken up.

00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:39.400 align:middle line:90%
She hears, "Rose.

00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:41.240 align:middle line:90%
Rose."

00:19:41.240 --> 00:19:43.020 align:middle line:90%
Rose wakes up.

00:19:43.020 --> 00:19:44.960 align:middle line:90%
She's in shock.

00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:46.390 align:middle line:90%
"Betty?

00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:47.530 align:middle line:90%
Betty, is that you?"

00:19:47.530 --> 00:19:48.330 align:middle line:90%
"Rose.

00:19:48.330 --> 00:19:50.060 align:middle line:90%
It's me.

00:19:50.060 --> 00:19:52.900 align:middle line:90%
It's me on the other side."

00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:53.700 align:middle line:90%
"Betty.

00:19:53.700 --> 00:19:55.290 align:middle line:90%
This is amazing.

00:19:55.290 --> 00:19:56.260 align:middle line:90%
What's it like?

00:19:56.260 --> 00:19:57.060 align:middle line:90%
What's it like?

00:19:57.060 --> 00:19:57.720 align:middle line:90%
We promised.

00:19:57.720 --> 00:19:58.520 align:middle line:90%
We cut a deal."

00:19:58.520 --> 00:20:02.440 align:middle line:90%
She said, "Well, it's amazing.

00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:05.320 align:middle line:84%
We have good news and
bad news for you Rose.

00:20:05.320 --> 00:20:08.410 align:middle line:90%
But first, we're young again.

00:20:08.410 --> 00:20:10.900 align:middle line:90%
We play softball every day.

00:20:10.900 --> 00:20:13.550 align:middle line:90%
We have a great time.

00:20:13.550 --> 00:20:15.670 align:middle line:90%
That's the good news."

00:20:15.670 --> 00:20:17.980 align:middle line:84%
"Well, Betty, what's
the bad news?"

00:20:17.980 --> 00:20:21.262 align:middle line:84%
"Rose, you're
pitching tomorrow."

00:20:21.262 --> 00:20:23.180 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: [LAUGHTER]

00:20:23.180 --> 00:20:24.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The afterlife.

00:20:24.670 --> 00:20:25.570 align:middle line:90%
I had to get that in.

00:20:25.570 --> 00:20:26.230 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: That's a great--

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:27.030 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:20:27.030 --> 00:20:28.390 align:middle line:90%
And it's probably accurate.

00:20:28.390 --> 00:20:28.760 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:20:28.760 --> 00:20:29.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It might be.

00:20:29.680 --> 00:20:33.040 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Because
their sense of time

00:20:33.040 --> 00:20:35.830 align:middle line:84%
is different from
our sense of time.

00:20:35.830 --> 00:20:37.420 align:middle line:84%
They're not allowed
to mess with us.

00:20:37.420 --> 00:20:37.900 align:middle line:84%
They're not allowed
to change anything.

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:39.134 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They don't know even
what time is on the other side,

00:20:39.134 --> 00:20:39.220 align:middle line:90%
do they?

00:20:39.220 --> 00:20:40.370 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: Well,
I think they do.

00:20:40.370 --> 00:20:40.910 align:middle line:90%
I think they do.

00:20:40.910 --> 00:20:42.076 align:middle line:90%
I think they're aware of it.

00:20:42.076 --> 00:20:43.339 align:middle line:90%
It's just a different--

00:20:43.339 --> 00:20:45.130 align:middle line:84%
I think that time exists
on the other side.

00:20:45.130 --> 00:20:46.840 align:middle line:84%
This is a debate
that people have.

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:49.020 align:middle line:84%
It's just not the
same as over here.

00:20:49.020 --> 00:20:51.620 align:middle line:84%
It's just relatively
completely different.

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:55.270 align:middle line:84%
So they're aware of things
that are likely outcomes.

00:20:55.270 --> 00:20:56.930 align:middle line:90%
They can't predict the future.

00:20:56.930 --> 00:20:58.210 align:middle line:90%
Nobody can.

00:20:58.210 --> 00:21:00.022 align:middle line:84%
But they can give
you likely outcomes.

00:21:00.022 --> 00:21:02.230 align:middle line:84%
They can say, "Well, if this
happens and that happens

00:21:02.230 --> 00:21:03.896 align:middle line:84%
and everybody does
what they're supposed

00:21:03.896 --> 00:21:06.130 align:middle line:90%
to do, then that will occur.

00:21:06.130 --> 00:21:08.770 align:middle line:90%
You will be pitching tomorrow."

00:21:08.770 --> 00:21:10.474 align:middle line:90%
But there's a possibility that--

00:21:10.474 --> 00:21:11.515 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It could happen.

00:21:11.515 --> 00:21:13.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTINI: --Rose
has a recovery.

00:21:13.120 --> 00:21:16.150 align:middle line:84%
She's dating a doctor, who
comes in and fixes her.

00:21:16.150 --> 00:21:18.470 align:middle line:90%
So it's likely outcomes.

00:21:18.470 --> 00:21:20.620 align:middle line:84%
But what you hear quite
a bit, as I have--

00:21:20.620 --> 00:21:23.380 align:middle line:84%
you talk to people
in this field--

00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:25.690 align:middle line:84%
and they'll tell
you, "Well, there

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:27.310 align:middle line:90%
is no time on the other side."

00:21:27.310 --> 00:21:30.310 align:middle line:84%
But I've just found
that it's relative time.

00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:33.940 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, I had
two years apart

00:21:33.940 --> 00:21:36.280 align:middle line:90%
from being in this classroom.

00:21:36.280 --> 00:21:38.642 align:middle line:90%
But it felt like 20 minutes.

00:21:38.642 --> 00:21:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Which was
nothing in time.

00:21:40.100 --> 00:21:41.929 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Yeah, a few minutes.

00:21:41.929 --> 00:21:42.970 align:middle line:90%
And so I've asked people.

00:21:42.970 --> 00:21:45.460 align:middle line:84%
One woman said to me, "I
experienced this lifetime

00:21:45.460 --> 00:21:46.880 align:middle line:90%
over 25 years.

00:21:46.880 --> 00:21:50.560 align:middle line:84%
But when I went back, it felt
like 10 minutes had gone by."

00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:53.300 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: How influential was
the late Michael Newton--

00:21:53.300 --> 00:21:55.630 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Michael Newton--
with your work?

00:21:55.630 --> 00:21:57.440 align:middle line:10%
>>MARTINI: Well, with
my work, of course,

00:21:57.440 --> 00:21:58.650 align:middle line:10%
it was really everything.

00:21:58.650 --> 00:22:00.850 align:middle line:84%
He was the guy who opened
up the rabbit hole.

00:22:00.850 --> 00:22:03.460 align:middle line:84%
Because he was a skeptic
about the afterlife.

00:22:03.460 --> 00:22:05.800 align:middle line:84%
He had been a skeptic
about his work.

00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:08.710 align:middle line:84%
He allowed me to be a
skeptic about everything

00:22:08.710 --> 00:22:10.570 align:middle line:90%
that I was seeing or saying.

00:22:10.570 --> 00:22:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And once I did my
first session--

00:22:12.760 --> 00:22:14.290 align:middle line:90%
like I said, I've done five--

00:22:14.290 --> 00:22:16.300 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I had
taken the red pill.

00:22:16.300 --> 00:22:19.030 align:middle line:10%
But then, when I started
researching it in depth,

00:22:19.030 --> 00:22:20.890 align:middle line:10%
I found that there
was a doctor--

00:22:20.890 --> 00:22:24.040 align:middle line:10%
a psychologist in New
Jersey, Dr. Helen Wambach,

00:22:24.040 --> 00:22:26.500 align:middle line:10%
who 10 years earlier
than Michael,

00:22:26.500 --> 00:22:27.880 align:middle line:10%
had done the same research.

00:22:27.880 --> 00:22:30.640 align:middle line:10%
Where she had people under
deep hypnosis talking

00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:33.890 align:middle line:10%
about choosing your lifetime.

00:22:33.890 --> 00:22:36.280 align:middle line:84%
Did you choose your lifetime,
et cetera, et cetera?

00:22:36.280 --> 00:22:37.600 align:middle line:90%
And you find these things.

00:22:37.600 --> 00:22:39.700 align:middle line:84%
But Michael-- in
Michael's case, he's

00:22:39.700 --> 00:22:43.330 align:middle line:84%
got so many hallmarks that are
important for us to examine.

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:46.570 align:middle line:84%
So you check out
of this lifetime.

00:22:46.570 --> 00:22:48.860 align:middle line:84%
You get to the
flipside, as I call it.

00:22:48.860 --> 00:22:51.220 align:middle line:84%
There's a council
that you might meet.

00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:54.760 align:middle line:84%
There is your soul guide that
you're going to run into.

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:56.110 align:middle line:90%
There are your soul mates.

00:22:56.110 --> 00:22:56.943 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Loved ones.

00:22:56.943 --> 00:22:58.150 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTINI: Your loved ones.

00:22:58.150 --> 00:23:01.150 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see
people in your soul group,

00:23:01.150 --> 00:23:02.980 align:middle line:90%
as Newton used to call it.

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:05.050 align:middle line:90%
Some that might disturb you.

00:23:05.050 --> 00:23:08.980 align:middle line:84%
Because there's the uncle
that I really didn't like.

00:23:08.980 --> 00:23:12.160 align:middle line:84%
But it turns out, he says
to you, "Don't you remember?

00:23:12.160 --> 00:23:14.830 align:middle line:84%
You asked me to be
the annoying uncle.

00:23:14.830 --> 00:23:16.987 align:middle line:84%
You asked me to play that
role in this lifetime.

00:23:16.987 --> 00:23:18.570 align:middle line:84%
And I said I didn't
want to, because I

00:23:18.570 --> 00:23:19.900 align:middle line:90%
did that in the Viking Era.

00:23:19.900 --> 00:23:21.200 align:middle line:90%
But I agreed.

00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:24.550 align:middle line:84%
Because you said, "I can
only learn this lesson

00:23:24.550 --> 00:23:28.030 align:middle line:84%
if you play the evil, drunk
uncle in this lifetime."

00:23:28.030 --> 00:23:29.840 align:middle line:84%
And I did it out of
my love for you."

00:23:29.840 --> 00:23:33.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: On "Flip Side," you
can see Michael Newton talking

00:23:33.130 --> 00:23:35.850 align:middle line:90%
in his entirety on Gaia.

